# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

llama.cpp's `common/chat.cpp` hosts a set of **specialized template handlers** — static functions that handle specific model families with unique token/tool-call formats that the generic autoparser cannot reliably process. Each handler is registered inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` via pattern-matching on the template source string.

The Ministral 3 / Magistral Large handler already handles Mistral-family templates that use `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]...[/SYSTEM_PROMPT]`. This task adds a **separate handler for the simpler Mistral Instruct v0.3 format**, which uses `[INST]/[/INST]` markers without a `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` wrapper, prepends system messages to the first user turn, and ends assistant turns with `</s>`.

**Constraint:** Only new code may be added — no existing handler bodies or the header (`common/chat.h`) may be modified.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `common/chat.cpp` | **Only file to edit.** Contains all static handlers + `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` |
| `common/chat.h` | Public interface — **do not touch** |
| `common/chat-peg-parser.h` | PEG builder API (`common_chat_peg_builder`) |
| `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja` | Reference Mistral `[INST]`-family template (has `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` — must NOT be captured by the new handler) |
| `models/templates/mistralai-Ministral-3-14B-Reasoning-2512.jinja` | Reference Ministral 3 template (has `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` — already handled) |
| `tests/test-chat.cpp` | Integration tests (`peg_tester`) — Nemo test at line 3141 must continue to pass |

---

## Existing Pattern to Follow

Every handler in `common/chat.cpp` follows this exact shape:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_<name>(
    const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
    const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;
    data.prompt           = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format           = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.preserved_tokens = { /* special tokens the tokenizer must not split */ };
    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return /* PEG expression */;
    });
    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

And it is registered in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` as:

```cpp
if (src.find("UNIQUE_MARKER") != std::string::npos && ...) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: <name>\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_<name>(tmpl, params);
}
```

---

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Add the new handler function

**Insert after** the closing `}` of `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3` (currently ends around line 1517) and **before** the `namespace workaround {` block (line 1519).

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 handler
// Format: system message prepended to first [INST] turn, user wrapped in [INST]/[/INST],
// assistant content followed by </s>.
// Ref: https://huggingface.co/mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt           = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format           = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.preserved_tokens = {
        "[INST]",
        "[/INST]",
    };

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.prefix(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

**Why this parser:** The Mistral v0.3 format places no structural tokens around the assistant's output; the model generates content immediately after `[/INST]`. `p.prefix(inputs.generation_prompt)` skips any trailing generation-prompt bytes, then `p.content(p.rest())` captures everything else as the assistant message content.

---

### Step 2 — Register in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`

**Insert immediately before** the final `return std::nullopt;` on line 1690 (after the GigaChatV3 block ends).

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - wraps user turns with [INST]/[/INST], prepends system to first
    // user turn, appends </s> after assistant turns.
    // Distinguished from Ministral/Magistral Large 3 by absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT].
    // [AVAILABLE_TOOLS] exclusion prevents capturing Nemo-style templates that carry
    // their own tool-call format and are correctly handled by the autoparser.
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: mistral-instruct-v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

**Detection rationale:**
| Check | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `[INST]` present | Identifies the Mistral `[INST]/[/INST]` family |
| `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent | Distinguishes from Ministral 3 / Mistral v7 (as specified by task) |
| `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` absent | Excludes Nemo and other tool-capable templates that rely on autoparser — prevents regression of the existing Nemo peg_tester tests |

---

## What Is NOT Changed

- `common/chat.h` — no new declarations needed; the handler is `static`
- `src/llama-chat.h` / `src/llama-chat.cpp` — the older enum-based system is unrelated
- Any existing handler function bodies

---

## Verification

1. **Build:** `cmake --build build -j$(nproc) --target common` — should compile with no errors.

2. **Existing Nemo test** (`test-chat.cpp` line 3141–3148):
   - Nemo template source contains `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]`, so our new check returns `false` and the autoparser continues to handle it — no regression.

3. **Manual smoke test** for a pure v0.3 template (no `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]`):
   ```
   ./llama-cli --chat-template mistral-v3 --prompt "Hello"
   ```
   Or pass a minimal Jinja template string containing `[INST]` but not `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` or `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]`, and verify `LOG_DBG` outputs "Using specialized template: mistral-instruct-v3".

4. **Unit tests:** `./tests/test-chat` (or `ctest -R test-chat`) should pass unchanged.

